post_text: Don't forget! The YMCA will be set up in front of the high school entrance on August 6th from 2-4, or until supplies last, to hand out one Play Pack per elementary family. On that day there will be signage instructing families how to proceed through the drive thru distribution of the Play Packs. Each family will be given a short demonstration of what is in the bag and potential games/activities that can be played with the equipment. A short survey will also be given to each family. The YMCA staff will be wearing masks and gloves during the entire event. If you have any questions please call 716-358-7058.

The Randolph Central School District has launched a new mobile app that will help students, parents, and community members keep up to date with what is happening on or around our campus. This app is new to our district, and we are still finalizing some details to create a one stop for everything about RCS. You can download the app for free from the Apple App Store or the Google Play Store.

Apple: https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/randolph-central-school-ny/id1465194264?ls=1&mt=8

Google: http://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.blackboard.community.randolphcsd

If you have any questions or problems with the app, please don’t hesitate to reach out to us at techsupport@randolphcsd.org

High school yearbooks have arrived! If you pre-ordered a yearbook, you may pick up your copy at the high school main entrance on Tuesday, July 28 between 8am and 2:30pm or between 5pm and 6pm. When you arrive, please stay in your vehicle with a mask on and a staff member will assist you with your order.

If you did not pre-order a yearbook and would like to purchase one, they are $55. Please call the high school main office at 358-7007 to reserve one. There are limited extra copies, so reservations will be on a first-come, first-serve basis. Thank you!

post_text:
What a wonderful day, RCS!! The weather was perfect and it was so nice to see all of you!! 😎

We want to take a few moments and thank the following groups for making today outstanding!

•Randolph Fire Department
•Randolph EMS
•East Randolph Fire Department
•Conewango Fire Department
•Coldspring Fire Department
•Cattaraugus County Sheriff
•Seneca Nation Marshalls
•RCS Transportation Staff
•RCS Staff
•RCS Teachers

Lastly, we want to send a HUGE thank you to our community for coming out and giving our teachers and staff a final “wave goodbye”!

Have a fantastic and safe summer, Cardinals!

post_text: Good Morning, Cardinals!! We will be hosting an End of the Year Sendoff Parade for all grades on Friday, June 12 starting at 9 a.m.. The East and West Routes are below. We wish we could drive by every house but due to the geographic miles within the district, sadly we cannot reach everyone. However, please feel free to review the routes and follow social distancing guidelines, and join us along the route where you would like. On Friday, we will post the routes again and have a turn by turn update as we move along the routes. We are SO excited to see you all! Please feel free to make signs, wear your RED and WHITE, and please post pictures on the Facebook route thread that morning! It’s A Great Day To Be A Cardinal!

5.18.20
Good Morning!
This is Superintendent Kaine Kelly with an important message from the Randolph Central School District regarding the end of the school year. Friday June 12th will be the last day of instruction for all students. The last day for instructional staff will be Tuesday June 16th and the last day of meal delivery will be Friday June 26th. Additional information will be forthcoming regarding the return of instructional and technology materials, summer school, the summer feeding program, and other end of the year events and procedures. If you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Thank you and have a great day!

post_text: Families across the country are adapting to the evolving changes in daily life caused by the COVID-19 pandemic. Most schools, places of public gathering, and nonessential businesses are closed, and parents and other caregivers are faced with helping their families adjust to the new normal. This includes trying to keep children occupied, feeling safe, and attempting to keep up with schoolwork as best as possible. None of this is easy, but it helps to stay focused on what is possible in order to reinforce a sense of control and to reassure children that they are okay, and that the situation will get better. Please check out the following resource from The National Association of School Psychologists.: Helping Children Cope With Changes Resulting From COVID-19.

Good Afternoon!
This is Superintendent Kaine Kelly with an informational message from the Randolph Central School District. Many of you may have heard the Governor's address this afternoon where he ordered a state wide lock-down of non essential businesses and placed new restrictions on NYS residents. This lock-down does not effect companies and services that are considered critical to public health and safety which our meal service is. We will continue to provide meal pick up and delivery next week as we have been. Also, in anticipation of this order we have already reduced our onsite workforce to be in compliance with the Governor's orders. Just wanted to keep you informed and aware. Please have a good weekend and enjoy this time with your families.

Thursday March 19, 2020

Randolph Central School District
First Responder/Medical Professional Childcare Plan

The Randolph Central School District is helping to coordinate childcare for any first responder or medical professional (EMTs, paramedics, nurses, doctors, nursing home employees, etc.). We have reached out to our community partners regionally to coordinate childcare solutions for our first responders who are in need. The following licensed childcare providers have availability and are willing to provide childcare.

Grammy’s Daycare
Location: Randolph (Sheldon St.)
Phone: 716-499-7114 (Kelly Mitchell)

Lynn’s Love Bugs Family Daycare
Location: Salamanca
Phone: 716-945-1945 (Lynn Harrington)

Olean YMCA
Location: Olean
Phone: 716-373-2400

YMCA Heritage House Child Care Center
Location: Jamestown
Phone: 716-338-0111

Please share this message with any first responders or medical professionals within your network. Thank you for your help in keeping our community safe and well cared for during this time.

post_text:
Check out the new addition to the RCS Technology Department; The Titan Series CNC Router.

The Titan is an industrial quality CNC Router featuring an air-cooled, 12 hp HSD automatic tool change spindle, allowing for more aggressive cutting and multiple tool operations. This machine is perfect for cabinet shops, furniture manufacturers, and any application using multiple tools to process each sheet or part.

We here at RCS along with Mr. Freeman, Mr. Peirson, and Mrs. Walker want our students to leave RCS with the skills they need to run an industrial grade CNC machine and meet the increasing labor demands of our region.

https://vimeo.com/384545943

post_text: Last night the Cardinal’s Nest welcomed back 2003 graduate Tim Bontemps who since graduating from RCS and St. Bonaventure has covered the NBA for the Washington Post and is currently employed by ESPN. Tim was named an Honorary Captain and the boys brought home a decisive victory in his honor last night! Last night’s visit was a great example for our student body that hard work and dedication can lead you to your dreams regardless of where you are from!
